==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bull brier
<hw>Bull" bri`er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species
of Smilax (<spn>Smilax Pseudo-China</spn>) growing from <state>New
Jersey</state> to the <geog>Gulf of Mexico</geog>, which has very large
tuberous and farinaceous rootstocks, formerly used by the Indians for a
sort of bread, and by the negroes as an ingredient in making beer; --
called also <altname>bamboo brier</altname> and <altname>China
brier</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bullcomber</ent>⟦br⟧
